      • write

        public void write(String name,
                  double[] pr,
                  double[] pi,
                  int[] dimensions)
           throws IOException
        Writes a double array variable to the MAT-file.
        Parameters:
        name - The name of the variable.
        pr - The real parts of the array elements.
        pi - The imaginary parts of the array elements (optional, must be the same length as pr if provided).
        dimensions - The array dimensions (there must be at least two dimensions and the product of the dimensions must be pr.length).
        Throws:
        IOException - if writing to the underlying stream fails.
        IllegalArgumentException - if pi != null and pi.length != pr.length.
        IllegalArgumentException - if the product of dimensions is not equal to pr.length.

      • write

        public void write(String name,
                  double[] pr,
                  double[] pi,
                  int[] dimensions,
                  boolean global)
           throws IOException
        Writes a double array variable to the MAT-file.
        Parameters:
        name - The name of the variable.
        pr - The real parts of the array elements.
        pi - The imaginary parts of the array elements (optional, must be the same length as pr if provided).
        dimensions - The array dimensions (there must be at least two dimensions and the product of the dimensions must be pr.length).
        global - A value indicating if the variable is to have global scope.
        Throws:
        IOException - if writing to the underlying stream fails.
        IllegalArgumentException - if pi != null and pi.length != pr.length.
        IllegalArgumentException - if the product of dimensions is not equal to pr.length.

      • write

        public void write(String name,
                  double[] pr,
                  double[] pi,
                  int[] dimensions,
                  int[] strides)
           throws IOException
        Writes a double array variable to the MAT-file.
        Parameters:
        name - The name of the variable.
        pr - The real parts of the array elements.
        pi - The imaginary parts of the array elements (optional, must be the same length as pr if provided).
        dimensions - The array dimensions (there must be at least two dimensions and the product of the dimensions must be pr.length).
        strides - The differences between indices into pr of consecutive entries along each dimension (must be equal in length to dimensions).
        Throws:
        IOException - if writing to the underlying stream fails.
        IllegalArgumentException - if pi != null and pi.length != pr.length.
        IllegalArgumentException - if the product of dimensions is not equal to pr.length.

        public void writeUnsigned(String name,
                          int[] array,
                          int[] dimensions,
                          boolean global)
                   throws IOException
        Writes an unsigned int array variable to the MAT-file.
        Parameters:
        name - The name of the variable.

        dimensions - The array dimensions (there must be at least two dimensions and the product of the dimensions must be array.length).

        Throws:
